SIMPLE: non-standard
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: non-standard
<hw>non-standard</hw></mhw> <pos>adj.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>varying from or not adhering to a standard; <as>as,
<ex>nonstandard</ex> windows; envelopes of <ex>nonstandard</ex> sizes;
<ex>non-standard</ex> lengths of board cost more per foot</as>. Opposite
of <ant>standard</ant>.</def> [Narrower terms: <stype>deficient,
inferior, substandard</stype>]⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> nonstandard.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Linguistics)</fld> <def>Not conforming to the
language usage of a prestige group within a community; <as>as, a
<ex>nonstandard</ex> dialect is one used by uneducated speakers or
socially disfavored groups</as>. Opposite of
<ant>standard</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>nonstarter</ent>⟦br⟧
